      • reentrantCheck

        public static java.lang.Object reentrantCheck(java.lang.Object currentInstance,
                                              java.lang.Object newInstance)
        Checks to see if creating the new instance has resulted in a recursive call. If it has, and the new instance is the same as the current instance, return the instance. However, if the new instance differs from the current instance, an IllegalStateException is thrown.
